  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Traditional HSI systems, often based on spatial and spectral scanning methods like push-broom or variable-filter systems, are generally bulky and slow.",
    "They also feature moving parts and require long exposure times (Arad et al. 2020).",
    "Additionally, the equipment used to capture hyperspectral images is typically expensive and complex (Gao et al. 2010; Salazar-Vazquez and Mendez-Vazquez 2020).",
    "Even with high-cost systems, image acquisition is time-consuming, a significant barrier to rapid, automated quality assessments in the agri-food sector.",
    "These systems also struggle with lower spatial resolution compared to conventional imaging methods, making it difficult to identify individual features within an image (Mei et al. 2022)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "They also feature moving parts and require long exposure times (Arad et al. 2020).",
    "Additionally, the equipment used to capture hyperspectral images is typically expensive and complex (Gao et al. 2010; Salazar-Vazquez and Mendez-Vazquez 2020).",
    "These systems also struggle with lower spatial resolution compared to conventional imaging methods, making it difficult to identify individual features within an image (Mei et al. 2022)."
